version: "1.0.5"
abstract: >
  30 agent sessions (4,306 messages) across three pre-registered controlled experiments
  testing whether prompt repetition improves LLM-agent task completion on structured
  software-engineering tasks. Null results across all three experiments; identifies
  ceiling effects and rubric-runner co-design failure as distinct evaluation failure modes.
